Reasoning: The paper focuses on the formal analysis of security mechanisms for V2X, specifically the revocation of malicious or misbehaving vehicles from the V2X system. This falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses cryptographic solutions and trusted hardware, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and cyber security (cs.CY). The use of formal analysis and prover also suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY), while the proposed extension of the REWIRE scheme involves the design of a new protocol, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
